File::Index Version 0.06

This module provides the 'indexf' and 'rindexf' functions which operate on files in the 
same way that the 'index' and 'rindex' functions operate on strings.  It can be used
where memory limitations prohibit the slurping of an entire file.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc File::Index

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=File-Index

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/File-Index

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/File-Index

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/File-Index/


